  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      For unilateral spinal block, spinal local anesthetics should take effect on the spinal nerves
      of one side. With full flexion of the spine, the cauda equina becomes tightened and hangs in
      the middle of the subarachnoid space. This study was performed to assess if flexion of the
      vertebral column facilitates unilateral spinal anesthesia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
